      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "WASHINGTON, April 20.-Mrs\nPhilander C. Knox, wife of the\nPennsylvania senator, is a near suf-\nfraget. She is a woman of strong\npersonality and pronounced opin-\nions. \"As a matter of principle\"\nshe says, 81 favor women having\na voice in matters where their ex-\nperience and sympathy make their\nopinion authoritative.\n\n\nEvery few women, believe,\nwould abuse the gift of suffrage;\nfewer perhaps than men who claim\nthis supreme privilege by inherent\nright. Women would devote them\nselves to that portion of the public"
    }
